Remarks: partly substituted (CAD, DDC, IDH, MDH) by Charaxes castor; COI sequence AY09021 of C. castor (voucher NW78-3) is 98.4% identical to European and 99.4% to African C. jasius; similarity of nuclear loci is between 98.7% (wingless) and 99.7% (EF-1a, RpS2, RpS5)

Full name: Pseudochazara orestes De Prins & van der Poorten, 1981
Pseudophilotes barbagiae De Prins & van der Poorten, 1982
Spialia rosae Hernández-Roldán, Dapporto, Dincă, Vicente & Vila, 2016
